<lb/><opener><dateline rend="right"><placeName><settlement type="town">Birkenhead</settlement></placeName> 
<lb/><date when="1858-03-06">6 March 
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/> 1858</date></dateline>
<lb/>   
<lb/><salute>My Dear <persName>Agnes</persName></salute></opener><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->

<lb/><p>The Pearl went 
<lb/>out of dock
<lb/>today &amp; sails 
<lb/>on <choice><sic>monday</sic><corr>Monday</corr></choice>
<lb/>forenoon, We
<lb/>go on <!--unclear word (board?) --> 
<lb/>at 8 am the morning 

	<pb facs="liv_001273_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/><persName>Mama</persName> has been
<lb/>putting all the
<lb/><!--unclear word--> in <persName>Mrs.
<lb/>Calein</persName> in order
<lb/><!--unclear word--> lends her
<lb/>love</p>        	
<lb/><p>Now you
<lb/>are commmitted
<lb/>to the caring
<lb/>God Almighty <!--Do I mark this as a religious term?--> 
<lb/>May he give

	<pb facs="liv_001273_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>you much
<lb/>grace and 
<lb/>be merciful
<lb/>to you. Write
<lb/>to <persName>Robert</persName>:
<lb/>Never do 
<lb/>anything you
<lb/>would be
<lb/>ashamed to

	<pb facs="liv_001273_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>and may the
<lb/>Lord be very 
<lb/>gracious to you
<lb/>Kind <!--unclear word (report? repent?)-->
<lb/>to your <term type="occupation">teacher</term>
<lb/>&amp; <!--unclear word--> also
<lb/>to <persName>Mr. Buchanan</persName> 
<lb/>when you see
<lb/>his <space dim="horizontal" extent="1" unit="words"/> <persName>Jesus</persName><!--Unclear word--></p>

        	</div>
